<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Veraphie on 04-25-2001 08:37 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Well, frankly, you WON'T have the AC/HP to tank for more than a couple of rounds post 50. Even if you go all out crazy on ac/hp equipment. Besides, that's stupid, root, or stun & root, then move away until tank is able to build up aggro before sitting down or you'll get summoned ^^. Why the hell should you be tanking when you have a whole line of roots and stuns? I doooo noooot understand.
Secondly, melee is stupid, i totally agree. Melee post 50 would just make me cringe. There's LOTS of things you can do when you have a lot of mana. Do a MoK and load three stuns, chain stun, see how much dmg your tank will take. Not very much. Personally I like nuking a lot too, our DD's aren't THAT bad, and my fave high lvl dungeon is HS anyway, which means lots of undead, lots of nuking opportunities =). Also when you're like lvl 57+ you can pull singles in OS, i've often acted as puller for my group. If i'm only online for not too long and just want to grind at seb zone for like an hour or something i won't even bother with an enc, get all melee, pull singles, root park any adds, MoK the mob, use my DE snare necklace. 5 melees in a group ROCKS, let me tell you, and it's also when MoK truly shines. I don't even bother with dispelling the mobs, MoK will cancel out most DS'es. Sooooo many things you can do besides just heal and buff and med on your ass.
And it's true, just keeping your group alive != good clericking. You should be keeping downtime to a minimum, and throwing in stuns/nukes to speed up the killing process, even. It's a great feeling when your group asks you, how do you pull, nuke every mob, stun all the gaters, snare the mob, and keep us all buffed and at good health with no med breaks ever? The answer is, ya don't melee!

Veraphie
58 Templar of Vazaelle
</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
